The Council met in an informal format, also known as an Arria Meeting, outside of the Council chamber amid concerns a low-level conflict in the Anglophone regions of the South-west and North-west is exacerbating humanitarian needs in the country affecting some 4.3 million people. 

The government has long rejected calls from separatists seeking independence rooted in long-standing claims of political and economic discrimination by Francophone authorities against the minority English-speaking population. 

Sherwin Bryce-Pease reports... --SABC--